<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A9206017" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Vehicle Height Sensor Inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A9206016">Rear Vehicle Height Sensor Removal and Installation</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear vehicle height sensor assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9206016"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Arrange 3 new 1.5 V batteries (1) in series (check that total voltage is 4.5 – 5.0 V), and connect it as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B920018.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "70.741mm" ver = "01" gw = "176" gh = "184"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Move arm (1) of rear vehicle height sensor as indicated in the figure to check output voltages at lowest position [a] and highest position [b]. Also check that output voltage gradually increases when arm and link set is moved slowly from lowest position to highest position. If check result is not as specified, replace rear vehicle height sensor.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A920009.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "56.091mm" ver = "01" gw = "166" gh = "142"/>
</figure>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A920006.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.614mm" ver = "03" gw = "179" gh = "104"/>
